Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Order for Appearance at Settlement Conference; Report to Court on Results of Settlement Conference.

1:07 PM Defendant Dustin P. Hartzell appeared by video, in custody from the Clark County Jail.   Attorney Kristi S. Tlusty in court for State of Wisconsin. Defendant does qualify for a public defender.  A public defender has not been appointed.  Court advises defendant of charges and penalties.  Defendant waives reading of the complaint.  Defendant waives his right to a timely preliminary hearing.  Bond continued.
Pre-trial conference scheduled for November 10, 2022 at 10:00 am.

10:00 a.m. Kristi Tlusty appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Defendant appeared in court in custody. Court found probable cause for the arrest. Court advised DE of possible charges and penalties. Court advised DE of right to attorney.  Notice of right to attorney given to defendant.  State requested a $3,000.00 signature bond with conditions of: going to the Taylor County Sheriff's Department for booking, Defendant shall not possess or consume any controlled substances without a valid prescription. Court ordered bond with conditions as requested.  Initial appearance set for September 20, 2022 at 1:00p.m.-JN

*Defendant shall not leave the State of Wisconsin without prior notice to and written approval of the Court.  Must report to the Taylor County Sheriff's Office for Booking Procedure. Defendant shall not possess or consume any controlled substances without a valid prescription.
